# codetracer-desktop capabilities file (CodeTracer Launcher spec §2.6).
#
# This file is the source of truth for the launcher's component
# discovery: when ct is installed as a launcher component, this file
# is copied to
#   <components-root>/codetracer-desktop@<version>/capabilities
# (see codetracer-launcher/src/install.nim and §2.3 of the spec).
#
# Key declarations:
#   * ``bin`` -- launcher uses this to find the binary inside the
#     component directory's ``bin/`` subdir.
#   * ``help-delegate`` -- marks codetracer-desktop as the launcher's
#     mandatory help delegate. ``ct --help`` / ``ct`` / ``ct completion``
#     all route to this binary's ct-help / ct-describe-commands /
#     ct-complete / ct-completions subcommands.
#   * ``<command> .ext1 .ext2 ...`` -- declares which file extensions
#     each command can handle (used by the launcher router to pick
#     the right component for ``ct record foo.py``).
#
# The dynamic, human-readable help content for these commands comes
# from running ``ct ct-describe-commands`` at runtime -- this static
# file is intentionally minimal.

name codetracer-desktop
bin codetracer
description CodeTracer desktop application -- launcher help delegate
help-delegate

record .py .rb .nr .styl .wasm
record-test .py .rb .nr
run .py .rb .nr .styl .wasm
replay
list
print
install
host
upload
download
login
edit
import
ci
help
remote
activate
check-license
